Art,<br><br>
I'm glad that I am able to jump in following your post which contains the spatz quote.<br><br>
An obvious thing that spatz misses is this: The Hyena pack and its Pack Mom and sis is evidence that we have found common ground as people. We have liberals, we have conservatives and we have &quot;tweeners&quot;. The purpose of this site has been for us to find each other by reaching out. As veterans we know what the truth is about Vietnam. <br><br>
And most importantly, as vets, we must accept the burden of being called murderers and baby killers TOGETHER. When we accept the bad along with the good (oh yes there was much good) we become strong. The words of our detractors can not hurt us. Those who second guess us have never walked in our shoes. It is very obvious to me.<br><br>
People like spatz don't want to see veterans of divergent views getting along and building trust among themselves. Why? Because the little voice that is whispering in HIS ear tells him that  his time has come and gone, while the time of the Vietnam Veteran has finally arrived. The little voice - that causes him to proclaim that he deserves mention via a Protestors Memorial - is frantically telling him that he is not top banana. He wants to be ringleader and the only possible way that will happen is if Veterans are divided.<br><br>
We HAVE had important dialogue on this site where we vehemently disagreed on the nature of the Vietnam War. Unfortunately it lies buried beneath reams of personal conflicts. It will be the chore of those who edit this site to sort it out.<br><br>
My point is this: readers and authors know where the principal characters of this site stand. It is needless to continue arguing. Our words speak for themselves AND THEY ARE POSTED ON THIS SITE. We all should be extremely proud of how far we have come in accepting our brothers as brothers -regardless of the ideology involved. This is maturity.<br><br>

<p><code>-- wingman*greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


